What I now did and trying out is a sliding window preloading so we start loading the next uid after we got the data from the previous one. This test run can be followed here and looking good so far. I think this is also why some UIDs got slashed when they actually uploaded a gradient. It seems to always be the first eval uid for a window which I believe is because we tried to get that gradient before the pre loading of the data was done. With the new sliding window pre-loading we will put less pressure on the network and it should make it better. Also, I increased the timeout in `s3_get_object` so we hopefully don't miss gradients when they actually exist. I will share a PR with these changes shortly
